t gap), inflation tends to be low, and when the economy is operating above its capacity (positive output gap), inflation tends to rise. Step 8: Conclusion - In conclusion, the Taylor rule provides a framework for monetary policy decisions based on the state of the economy relative to its productive capacity and inflation targets. Each component of the rule serves to guide the central bank in balancing its dual mandate of price stability and maximum employment."
