m holding the stock. This can be represented as $k > \frac{u(\text{sell}) - u(\text{hold})}{u(\text{sell}) - u(\text{hold})}$, which simplifies to $k > 1$ under the assumption that $u(\text{sell}) > u(\text{hold})$. Therefore, the investor will choose to hold the losing stock if $k > 1$, indicating a high degree of regret aversion."
