he conditions under which monetary policy is more effective - Monetary policy is more effective than fiscal policy when the money demand is less interest-sensitive (small 'f') and when the IS curve is more unstable than the LM curve. In these conditions, changes in the money supply have a larger impact on output, and pursuing a money supply target leads to smaller output fluctuations."
